COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. Delight Ward MERNER, Respondent. No. 8023. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 13, 1935. Arthur H. Kent, Acting Asst. Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. J. Lenox Ward, of Oakland, Cal., for respondent.

Before WILBUR, DENMAN, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for petitioner, consented to by counsel for respondent, ordered, petition to review dismissed; mandate forthwith.
